			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">/viewport left top width height
<br />

<br />
The top left corner of the screen is 0,0.
<br />

<br />
The default viewport is the entire screen, so in your resolution /viewport default is the same as /viewport 0, 0, 1024, 768.
<br />

<br />
/viewport 192 0 640 480 will create a smaller view centered horizontally at the top of the screen.  (1024-640)/2 = 192 to find the right left edge value for centering.
<br />

<br />
/viewport 0 0 600 450 for a window in top left corner
<br />

<br />
To maintain the same aspect ratio, width and height need to be in a 4-3 ratio (that's when width/4 = height/3)...but it's not required if you like the skewed view. Try /viewport 0, 0, 1024, 400 for instance.
<br />

<br />
Experiment. You can make the 3-d window almost any size and place it anywhere on your screen.  The 2-d user interface can still be placed anywhere on the screen.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
