			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">To prove that it's not just a mask, try this:
<br />

<br />
/viewport 0,0,800,600
<br />

<br />
Look at some NPC who will not walk away. Position him so that his head is near the top of the viewable area, and his feet are near the bottom.
<br />

<br />
/viewport 200,100,600,400
<br />

<br />
This will shrink the viewport to half height and half width, leaving the center in place for easy viewing.
<br />

<br />
Flip back and forth between the two viewports, using shift-up to repeat the commands. You'll see that the NPC is shrunk in the second viewport, and his head and feet are still visible. If it was just a mask, you would see his head and feet cut off.
<br />

<br />
Now, if you change the height-width ratio of the viewport (going from a 800x600, which is 4:3, to 700x700, which is 1:1, for example) you will get some stuff cut off, because EQ will not "stretch out" the 3D graphics to match your viewport's ratio.<br />_________________<br /><br><div align=center><img src="http://www.shootingiron.com/tipop/notherkrag.jpg" width="500" height="200" border="0" usemap="#nothermap"><map name="nothermap"><area alt="Fury of Faith" coords="31,157,152,187" href="http://members.telocity.com/~Tipop2000/fury"><area alt="Tipop's Homepage" coords="186,157,321,187"  href="http://members.telocity.com/~Tipop2000/"><area alt="Kraggan's Magelo Profile" coords="342,157,465,186" href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=120506"></map></div></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
